## Market Landscape & Strategic Recommendations

### Market Size (2025-2033 Estimates)

| Metric | 2025/2026 | 2030/2033 | CAGR |
|--------|-----------|-----------|------|
| Edge AI market (proxy for local LLMs) | $24.91B | $118.69B (2033) | ~22% |
| Broader LLM market | $10.97B (2026) | $32.5B (2030) | ~31% |

*No universally accepted "local LLM" category exists in vendor reports. Edge AI revenue is the pragmatic proxy.*

---

### Strategic Recommendations

**1. Start narrow, not broad.** Pick *one* high-signal use case:
   - Sensitive document Q&A (compliance data stays on-prem)
   - Repeated internal workflow assistant (documented ROI)
   - Factory/retail edge deployments (offline operation requirements)

**2. Small/mid open models first.** 7B-14B parameter models are sufficient for 70-80% of enterprise tasks when properly fine-tuned or prompted. Don't over-provision.

**3. Architect for hybrid from day one.** The cloud isn't going to be replaced locally for most orgs. The question is routing: "80% of queries handled locally + 20% escalated to cloud for ambiguous/hard tasks."

